    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 151 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="to"
                            >Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d151fn1">Sent by the United States Military Attaché, London,
                        via Army channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-10">10 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>.
                    Personal and top secret. Number 83.</p>
                <p>Thank you for your Number 65.<note n="2" xml:id="d151fn2">Not printed. This
                        message informed <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1">Churchill</persName>
                        concerning the final text of <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>’s
                        reply to <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName>’s message of May 27
                        concerning the establishment of diplomatic relations with <persName
                            corresp="#p_B5">Bulgaria</persName>, Finland, Hungary, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_R3">Rumania</persName>. Cf. <ref target="#d285fn5">document
                            No. 285, footnote 5</ref>.</note> I have sent the following: to
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Prime Minister to <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Marshal
                            Stalin</persName>. 10th June 1945.</p>
                        <p>“Thank you for your message of the 27th May<note n="3" xml:id="d151fn3"
                                >Text in <hi rend="italic">
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName>’s
                                    Correspondence</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                                361.</note> informing me that you think the time has come to resume
                            diplomatic relations with Roumania, <persName corresp="#p_B5"
                                >Bulgaria</persName> and Finland with the possibility that a similar
                            action can be taken with regard to Hungary in the near future.</p>
                        <p>“2. We have ourselves been considering our future relations with these
                            states and we hope very shortly to put comprehensive proposals before
                            you and the United States Government. I should hope that we might then
                            discuss them when next we meet.”<note n="4" xml:id="d151fn4">Cf. <hi
                                    rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 363.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
